  "body": "I'm running Kubernetes under Docker (following [this](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/docs/getting-started-guides/docker-multinode/master.md) guide). I tried to set up an RC that would run a registry:2 container and attach a gitRepo volume with the SSL certs I want to use. When I run it though, I get this error: \n `Error syncing pod, skipping: failed to exec 'git clone git@gitrepo': : exec: \"git\": executable file not found in $PATH`  \nIf k8s supports git repositories as volumes though, it feels like the executable should be included in the container.\n",
